column5: im in tears as i type this just put my snowmobile away for the season......hurry up winter come back anyone else gonna miss the snow???
I'm not going to miss it at all.  Not a single flake.  Bring on the soft water!!!
I hope too get on cooks bay a couple more times  but I am ready for open water, time to go get the boat
What is all this "snow" stuff I keep hearing aboot???

As much as I enjoy fishing in the boat - there is just something special about spending the weekend out on the ice, and staying over night in the hut - yes - I already do miss it.  oh well - Jan 01 will be here soon enough - and am looking forward to it!  Don
Yup!... I think senility is setting in on the old lookin' guy!!!
I just got a snowmobile and have to wait a year to use it
You guys can keep your snow & ice, but I've got a brand new boat & motor sitting on a trailer that needs SOFT water to work properly
LOL - even Miss Kelly enjoyed the weekend out in the hut!    senile like a fox!  Don
uh-HUH!!!... and I suspect that she was the one that caught Team #5's latest 11" Perch entry!!!
Gad minus 9 tomorrow, I bet I wont be fishing the Longweeknd in May as there will still be ice.
Something you Hillbillies don't see that often  Steve
I think we planned it that way Bubba!!!
I sold my sled in January hoping someone would take the hint and get the soft water here ASAP! No such luck.
Today was a sad day.  I do hope to hit simcoe for perch a few more times though...
Nope can't wait for the soft water and taking off the shrink wrap it's gonna be like Christmas WOOT WOOT
